-- Portugal’s Unemployment Rate Rose to 15.8% in the Third Quarter
-- B y   J o a o   L i m a
-- 2012-11-14T11:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-14/portugal-s-unemployment-rate-rose-to-15-8-in-the-third-quarter.html
Portugal ’s  jobless rate  rose to a
euro-era record of 15.8 percent in the three months through
September as the country’s economy contracted for an eighth
quarter.  The unemployment rate increased from 15 percent in the
second quarter and 12.4 percent in the third quarter of 2011,
the Lisbon-based National Statistics Institute said today in an
e-mailed statement.  The government predicts the unemployment rate will rise to
16.4 percent for all of 2013 from 15.5 percent this year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Joao Lima in Lisbon at 
